Most likely conclusion

The alarm pattern suggests:

Heavy PS traffic
   ↓
DMP database/storage latency
   ↓
Shared filesystem access timeout
   ↓
CMP SHARED disk-access-fail
   ↓
CMP LOG disk-access-fail
   ↓
PM collection failure
   ↓
Storage recovered automatically

Since:

pods never restarted,

alarms auto-cleared,

multiple components affected simultaneously,


this is unlikely to be:

application crash,

container issue,

Kubernetes scheduling issue.


It is more likely:

storage backend latency,

filesystem stall,

or node disk I/O bottleneck during heavy multiplexing traffic.
